Subject: [PATCH] build.rs: build the OpenGL backend with EGL instead of GLX/X11

maplibre-native-rs 0.8.2 builds maplibre-native's OpenGL backend on Linux with
GLX, which transitively requires X11 (it links X11 and uses XInitThreads). That
cannot run on a headless / console-only box with no X server, which is exactly
this SPI panel's setup (surfaceless EGL + software GL to /dev/fb0).

This switches the Linux OpenGL build to EGL: configure maplibre-native with
-DMLN_WITH_EGL=ON -DMLN_WITH_X11=OFF and link EGL instead of X11. It matches the
runtime env used here (EGL_PLATFORM=surfaceless LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1
GALLIUM_DRIVER=llvmpipe).

Apply to a local copy of the maplibre_native 0.8.2 crate source, then point the
app at it via [patch.crates-io] (see ../README.md). Candidate for upstreaming as
a selectable EGL backend in maplibre-native-rs.

--- a/build.rs
+++ b/build.rs
@@ -381,8 +381,9 @@
         GraphicsRenderingAPI::OpenGL => {
             config.configure_arg("-DMLN_WITH_OPENGL=ON");
             #[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
-            // GLX headless backend transitively requires X11.
-            config.configure_arg("-DMLN_WITH_X11=ON");
+            config.configure_arg("-DMLN_WITH_EGL=ON");
+            #[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
+            config.configure_arg("-DMLN_WITH_X11=OFF");
         }
         GraphicsRenderingAPI::Vulkan => {
             config.configure_arg("-DMLN_WITH_VULKAN=ON");
@@ -564,8 +565,7 @@
         GraphicsRenderingAPI::OpenGL => {
             println!("cargo:rustc-link-lib=GL");
             if cfg!(target_os = "linux") {
-                // GLX backend uses X11 symbols such as XInitThreads.
-                println!("cargo:rustc-link-lib=X11");
+                println!("cargo:rustc-link-lib=EGL");
             }
         }
         GraphicsRenderingAPI::Metal => {
